[normal]Last year the RLA and the Scottish Association of Landlords (SAL) conducted a survey of members to assess attitudes towards Universal Credit. Between 2
[normal]2nd October and 5th November 2012, 1,023 landlords from across the UK took part in the survey.  Results showed that 65.2 per cent of respondents do not support the Governme
[normal]nt’s plans for universal credit
[normal].
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The full results from the survey can be found at: 
[normal]http://news.rla.org.uk/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/universal-credit.rla-sal-survey-results-and-comments.051112.pdf
